You must pick a size category in which to specialize.  Remember
that each size also gives specialization in the next larger
size; 'small' is really small and medium, 'medium' gives medium
and large, and 'large' allows use of large and huge weapons.

Small weapons:   daggers, saps, small short swords, hand axes, etc.
Medium weapons:  larger short swords, maces, clubs, longer swords
Large weapons:   longswords, battleaxes, long maces, shorter staves
Huge weapons:    awl pikes, two-handed swords, greatbows, long staves

You may choose a damage type or combination to specialize in.
Damage types are slash, pierce, blunt, and cleave, and you
may choose none, one, or two of these types.  If you choose
two, a weapon must have both types in order to fit into your
specialty.

Slash:  Most sword variants, naginata, some polearms
Pierce:  daggers, rapiers, spears, bows, wooden stakes
Blunt:   staves, maces, clubs, hammers, rocks
Cleave:  axes, halberds, cleavers, some polearms

Note that there is some overlap, but not much. Some shortswords
are almost equally usable as piercing weapons or slashing weapons.
Some polearms are fitted with two different kinds of surfaces
for harming a foe, such as a halberd's iron spike for piercing
and wide blade for cleaving. But the majority of weapons on
Darkwind are one type only.

Finally, you may choose to specialize in missile or pole
weapons.  If you do not specify, then you will train in
normal melee (non-pole, non-missile) weapons.

Missile:  bows, crossbows, slings, throwing daggers, darts
Pole:     most staves, halberds, spears, tridents, etc.
